"Shutting down Squid can take a while, because Squid waits up to half a "
"minute before dropping the connections to the clients and writing its data "
"to the disk (see <option>shutdown_lifetime</option> option in <filename>/etc/"
"squid/squid.conf</filename> ),"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_proxy.xml:523
#, no-c-format
msgid "Terminating Squid"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_proxy.xml:524
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Terminating Squid with <command>kill</command> or <command>killall</command> "
"can damage the cache. To be able to restart Squid, damaged caches must be "
"deleted."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_proxy.xml:533
#, no-c-format
msgid "Removing Squid"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_proxy.xml:534
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Removing Squid from the system does not remove the cache hierarchy and log "
"files. To remove these, delete the <filename>/var/cache/squid</filename> "
"directory manually."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_proxy.xml:542
#, no-c-format
msgid "Local DNS Server"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_proxy.xml:543
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Setting up a local DNS server makes sense even if it does not manage its own "
"domain. It then simply acts as a caching-only name server and is also able "
"to resolve DNS requests via the root name servers without requiring any "
"special configuration (see <xref linkend=\"sec.dns.bind\"/> ). How this can "
"be done depends on whether you chose dynamic DNS during the configuration of "
"the Internet connection."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_proxy.xml:553
#, no-c-format
msgid "Dynamic DNS"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_proxy.xml:555
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Normally, with dynamic DNS, the DNS server is set by the provider during the "
"establishment of the Internet connection and the local <filename>/etc/resolv."
"conf</filename> file is adjusted automatically. This behavior is controlled "
"in the <filename>/etc/sysconfig/network/config</filename> file with the "
"<constant>NETCONFIG_DNS_POLICY</constant> sysconfig variable. Set "
"<constant>NETCONFIG_DNS_POLICY</constant> to <constant>\"\"</constant> with "
"the &yast; sysconfig editor."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_proxy.xml:565
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Then, add the local DNS server in the <filename>/etc/resolv.conf</filename> "
"file with the IP address <systemitem class=\"ipaddress\">127.0.0.1</"
"systemitem> for <systemitem class=\"domainname\">localhost</systemitem> . "
"This way, Squid can always find the local name server when it starts."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_proxy.xml:573
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To make the provider's name server accessible, specify it in the "
"configuration file <filename>/etc/named.conf</filename> under "
"<systemitem>forwarders</systemitem> along with its IP address. With dynamic "
"DNS, this can be achieved automatically when establishing the connection by "
"setting the sysconfig variable <constant>NETCONFIG_DNS_POLICY</constant> to "
"<constant>auto</constant> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_proxy.xml:584
#, no-c-format
msgid "Static DNS"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_proxy.xml:586
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With static DNS, no automatic DNS adjustments take place while establishing "
"a connection, so there is no need to change any sysconfig variables. "
"However, you must specify the local DNS server in the file <filename>/etc/"
"resolv.conf</filename> as described in <xref linkend=\"vle.squid.dynamicdns"
"\"/> . Additionally, the provider's static name server must be specified "
"manually in the <filename>/etc/named.conf</filename> file under "
"<systemitem>forwarders</systemitem> along with its IP address."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_proxy.xml:600
#, no-c-format
msgid "DNS and Firewall"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_proxy.xml:601
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you have a firewall running, make sure DNS requests can pass it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_proxy.xml:609
#, no-c-format
msgid "The &yast; Squid Module"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_proxy.xml:610
#, no-c-format
msgid "The &yast; Squid module contains the following tabs:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_proxy.xml:613
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Start-Up</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_proxy.xml:615
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies how Squid is started and which Firewall port is open on which "
"interfaces."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_proxy.xml:620
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>HTTP Ports</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_proxy.xml:622
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Define all ports where Squid will listen for HTTP requests from clients."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_proxy.xml:628
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Refresh Patterns</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_proxy.xml:630
#, no-c-format
msgid "Defines how Squid treats objects in the cache."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_proxy.xml:634
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Cache Settings</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_proxy.xml:636
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Defines settings in regard to cache memory, maximum and minimum object size, "
"and more."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_proxy.xml:643
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Cache Directory</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_proxy.xml:645
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Defines the top-level directory where Squid stores all cache swap files."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_proxy.xml:651
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Access Control</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_proxy.xml:653
#, no-c-format
